From Gordon Banks Subject Re Surgery of damaged tendons and median nerve In article writes I thought I will explore the net wisdom with the following questions Is there any better way to control the pain than what the surgeon suggested How long will such pain last Will the pain recur in the future No one can answer If she gets reflex sympathetic dystrophy it could last Just hope she does Most don' Do damaged partially cut tendons heal completely and is all of the finger strength regained How long does it take for the complete healing process Sometimes they do and sometimes they don' You just have to do the best job you can reattaching and You should know in a few Gordon Banks Skepticism is the chastity of the intellect and it is shameful to surrender it too